The paper deals with the problem of transmission of correlated sources over a fading multiple access channel (MAC) with partial channel state information available at both the encoders and the decoder. This problem falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) as it deals with the fundamental limits of communication over a noisy channel. The paper also discusses power allocation strategies, which is a topic in wireless communication (cs.MM). The use of partial channel state information is a common theme in signal processing (cs.SI) and networking (cs.NI). Finally, the paper deals with the transmission of data over a multiple access channel, which is a topic in communication systems (cs.COMM).
